-----------------------------------------------------------

--- Comprehensive .gitignore for Python ML/Data Science ---

-----------------------------------------------------------

1. Python Artifacts and Environments

pycache/
*.py[cod]
*.so

Virtual Environments

venv/
env/
.env

2. Data and Processing Artifacts

Raw and processed data (Crucial for keeping repo size down)

dataset/
data/
*.csv
*.tsv
*.xlsx
*.parquet
*.jsonl
*.feather

3. Model Weights and Serialization

*.pt
*.pth
*.onnx
*.h5

Common ML serialization formats

*.pkl
*.pickle
*.joblib
*.weights # Used by Darknet/some other frameworks

4. YOLO Specific & Caching

runs/       # Ultralytics training/detection output
wandb/      # Weights & Biases logging data
*.cache     # Roboflow/Ultralytics cache files
tmp/        # General temporary directory

5. Notebooks, Logs, and OS Files

.ipynb_checkpoints/ # Jupyter Notebook checkpoints
*.log
logs/
.DS_Store   # macOS
Thumbs.db   # Windows

6. IDE and Editor Files

.vscode/
.idea/

7. Documentation and Assets (Explicitly KEEP)

Files starting with '!' are explicitly tracked by Git.

!docs/
!assets/
!examples/
